topic.body:
I'm trying to increase the comment limits for users on two of my ZeroTalk clone zites.  I change only the numbers in /data/users/content.json.  I hit sign and publish /data/users/content.jason in the site control side bar.  The changes are successfully sent to 5 peers.  A few seconds later, my /data/users/content.json file is overwritten with the old values.  Essentially, ZeroNet rejects my changes.  I have never had this problem before.

Here is an example of the very end of one of my /data/users/content.json files:

  "content_inner_path": "data/users/content.json",
  "optional": null,
  "permission_rules": {
   ".*": {
    "files_allowed": "data.json",
    "max_size": 50000
   },
   "bitid/.*@zeroid.bit": {"max_size": 40000},
   "bitmsg/.*@zeroid.bit": {"max_size": 15000}
  },
  "permissions": {
   "bad@zeroid.bit": false,
   "k297rf@zeroid.bit": {"max_size": 100000},
   "soulscience@zeroid.bit": {"max_size": 150000},
   "xcape2net@zeroid.bit": {"max_size": 1000000}
  },
  "relative_path": "content.json"
 }
}

The only changes I am making are to the numbers.  What am I doing wrong?

