In data/1EARsQrEV4pqMnYRVECG9zenfnaGi5qzUT/data/content.json, at the very the bottom, you'll see something like:

  "content_inner_path": "data/users/content.json",
  "optional": null,
  "permission_rules": {
   ".*": {
    "files_allowed": "data.json",
    "max_size": 50000
   },
   "bitid/.*@zeroid.bit": {"max_size": 40000},
   "bitmsg/.*@zeroid.bit": {"max_size": 15000}
  },
  "permissions": {
   "bad@zeroid.bit": false,
   "xcape2net@zeroid.bit": {"max_size": 100000}
  },
  "relative_path": "content.json"
 }
}

The default limit for all users (in bytes) is set by:

   "max_size": 50000

Limits for specific users are set by:

   "bitid/.*@zeroid.bit": {"max_size": 40000},
   "bitmsg/.*@zeroid.bit": {"max_size": 15000}

   "xcape2net@zeroid.bit": {"max_size": 100000}

1630436341_1Cy3ntkN2GN9MH6EaW6eHpi4YoRS2.body:
> [gitcenter](#comment_1548_1Cy3ntkN2GN9MH6EaW6eHpi4YoRS2nK5Di): You also have to patch the certSelect call in js/all.js.

I forgot about that.  Thanks.

In file ZeroNet-py3/data/<new website data file>/js/all.js

replace all occurences of Page.cmd("certSelect", [["zeroid.bit", "kxoid.bit"]]);

with:

Page.cmd("certSelect", [["zeroid.bit", "kxoid.bit", "08chan", "cryptoid.bit", "kaffie.bit", "nanasi", "zeroverse.bit", "zv.znonymous"]]);
